SIMPLE: dispone
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dispone
<hw>Dis*pone"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>disponere</ets>. See <er>Disposition</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>To dispose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To dispose of.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>To make over, or convey,
legally.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He has <qex>disponed</qex> . . . the whole estate.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disponee</ent>⟦br⟧
